<div id="review_67115572" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/67115572" />
    <a title="Summer" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/2274107-summer"><img alt="Summer" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1591129956p2/2274107.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/67115572?book_show_action=true">Aug 12, 2009</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Summer" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Summer" href="/user/show/2274107-summer">Summer</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="did not like it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">did not like it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2274107-summer?shelf=historical-romance">historical-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2274107-summer?shelf=romance">romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2274107-summer?shelf=did-not-finish">did-not-finish</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/2274107-summer?shelf=hero-is-a-jerk">hero-is-a-jerk</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer67115572" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16425346476917146907">I only got a few chapters into this book and set it down. The hero is with his mistress at the beginning of the book and he&apos;s decided that he&apos;s bored of her. He decides to tell her the affair is over after a big social engagement they&apos;re attending. His mistress can tell his affections are waning and tries to bait the hero into marriage which doesn&apos;t work. Then it switches to the heroine and her family and all their relatives are listed as they get ready for a big social event. Then the heroine g</span>
  <span id="freeText16425346476917146907" style="display:none">I only got a few chapters into this book and set it down. The hero is with his mistress at the beginning of the book and he's decided that he's bored of her. He decides to tell her the affair is over after a big social engagement they're attending. His mistress can tell his affections are waning and tries to bait the hero into marriage which doesn't work. Then it switches to the heroine and her family and all their relatives are listed as they get ready for a big social event. Then the heroine goes all 'Woe is me!' because she's beautiful and well off but hasn't yet found a husband. Her four uncles haven't liked any of her choices in men and she doesn't know what to do and... blah blah blah. <br /><br />I like rakish hero's but the one in here didn't feel charming to me. The heroine's personality didn't feel engaging and her oh-so-sad plight of being beautiful and unmarried turned me off. I think this is probably more a case of not my cup of tea than anything, but whatever it is I couldn't finish it.</span>
  <a data-text-id="16425346476917146907" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
