    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_3847954303" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3847954303" />
    <a title="Christi (christireadsalot)" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/106618742-christi-christireadsalot"><img alt="Christi (christireadsalot)" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1605083674p2/106618742.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3847954303?book_show_action=true">Feb 20, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Christi (christireadsalot)" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Christi (christireadsalot)" href="/user/show/106618742-christi-christireadsalot">Christi (christireadsalot)</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Mass Market Paperback " href="/book/show/16121123-love-only-once">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/106618742-christi-christireadsalot?shelf=marriage-of-convenience">marriage-of-convenience</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/106618742-christi-christireadsalot?shelf=historical-romance">historical-romance</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/106618742-christi-christireadsalot?shelf=book-club">book-club</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3847954303" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8702977227043150934">4.5 stars (rounded up)<br/>Love Only Once is the first book in Johanna Lindsey’s beloved Malory series and I was excited to read it as a book club pick diving into older historical romances. I had only read 1 JL before this but own so many of her books, she’s one of those authors who’s backlist is overwhelming of knowing where to start. So this was a really great series to begin with I think! I totally get why the Malory series is one of her most-loved and was honestly surprised it was written in 198</span>
  <span id="freeText8702977227043150934" style="display:none">4.5 stars (rounded up)<br />Love Only Once is the first book in Johanna Lindsey’s beloved Malory series and I was excited to read it as a book club pick diving into older historical romances. I had only read 1 JL before this but own so many of her books, she’s one of those authors who’s backlist is overwhelming of knowing where to start. So this was a really great series to begin with I think! I totally get why the Malory series is one of her most-loved and was honestly surprised it was written in 1985, it really stood the test of time and I actually loved this! I think if you enjoy the big family dynamics like Bridgerton, this is a fun one. 💕<br /><br />Lady Regina “Reggie” Ashton (19 when the story starts) is a niece of the Malory family (Lord Edward Malory’s niece and first cousin to his large brood of children). Her 4 Uncles raised her after her parents died when she was just 2-years-old and she split her time amongst all of their homes. <br /><br />When Reggie borrows a carriage from another lady, she ends up being mistakenly seen by Nicholas as someone else (Nicholas’ former mistress) and being in the wrong place at the wrong time, she finds herself thrown over Nicholas’ horse and kidnapped right off the sidewalk. He then deposits her at his home and locks her in a room while he sets off to enjoy a ball he knew his former mistress (who he thinks he just locked up) was excited for. 🤣 Reggie figures out what is going on &amp; is just so amused by the entire situation and wishes she was at the ball to see Nicholas face when he spots his not-kidnapped lady there. Which of course does happen and he rushes back to make amends for his mistake, but then is so taken with Reggie who finds the entire thing so funny. This entire scene was just epic and I loved the drama of it all! 🤣 And I will say none of this was done in ill-will, Nicholas has zero hard feelings toward his former mistress and is doing this all cheekily for fun. Nicholas &amp; Reggie think no harm is done and they can return back to life as normal, but of course word gets out and everyone assumes Reggie has been compromised and we all know where that leads... While Reggie is down for getting married, Nicholas doesn’t want to ever marry (for reasons dealing with his past) and tries to convince her away from him.<br /><br />I loved the Malory family and all the dynamics, I loved how open Nicholas &amp; Reggie were with wanting one another (in the beginning at least), both Reggie &amp; Nicholas have a great sense of humor and their bantery dialogue was so fun! I loved that we have a rakish hero and the heroine thinks it’ll be a fun challenge to try &amp; reform him. 😆 I loved a lot of scenes in the last half of the book, it becomes a bit second chance. And I loved Reggie’s relationship with her Uncles, she definitely has them wrapped around her finger and just loved her wild, huge family. <br /><br />“Eden men do make exceptional husbands, for they love only once.”</span>
  <a data-text-id="8702977227043150934" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


